Similar to the scatterplots, you can observe relationships and variations in the dependent variable ("total") concerning the respective independent variables. For example, in the "Line Plot: Total vs Not Distracted," it appears that as the number of accidents where distraction was not a factor ("not_distracted") increases, the total number of accidents also tends to increase.
